===Etymology===
Thought by classical commentators to be the same word as {{och-l|冥|dark, black (of water)}} (likely in light of the parallelism with the unrelated {{och-l|海|sea, ocean}} < {{och-l|晦|dark}}). If so, see {{och-l|冥}} for etymology.

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} proposes that there is an outside chance this can be instead connected with {{cog|tbq-pro|*mlik}}, whence {{cog|obr|မ္လစ်|t=river}}, {{cog|my|မြစ်}}, {{cog|rki|tr=mreik|t=sea}}, {{cog|dao|tr='''mlik''' (tui)|t=big water, river, sea}}

